import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['cx'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['cx'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['cx'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['cx'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['cx'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude coordinates of the centroids of London boroughs?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['cy'], bins=10, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['cy'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["cy"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude coordinates of the centroids of London boroughs?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sorted_data = data.sort_values('cx', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(sorted_data['name'], sorted_data['cx'])
    plt.axhline(y=sorted_data['cx'].max(), color='r', linestyle='-',
                label=f"Max Longitude: {sorted_data['cx'].max():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("Which London borough has the highest longitude coordinate of its centroid?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['cx'], data['cy'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('Is there any correlation between the longitude and latitude coordinates of the centroids of London boroughs?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
